# Lifecycle & restart policies

```
create      start      stop/kill/exit      rm
image в”Җв–ә created в”Җв–ә running в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә stopped в”Җв–ә gone
                     в”Ӯ в–І  pause      в”Ӯ
                     в–ј в”Ӯ  unpause    в”Ӯ start
                    paused в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
```

- **`create`** вҖ” the unseen half of `run` (writable layer + config, not started).
- **`pause` / `unpause`** вҖ” freeze/thaw all processes via the freezer cgroup.

## Restart policies (survive crashes + reboots)

| Policy | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| **`no`** | default вҖ” never. |
| **`on-failure[:N]`** | only on non-zero exit. |
| **`always`** | any exit + daemon start (back after reboot). |
| **`unless-stopped`** | like `always`, but a manual `stop` sticks. **Prod choice.** |

Backoff is **exponential** (~1 min cap); the counter resets after 10s healthy.
